ONS is distributed with the GNU autotools. However, there are ways to install
ONS on platforms without the GNU autotools. For further information look into
the documentation.

Autotools:
Please change into the ./libraries directory and execute the common commands to
install programs with the GNU autotools:
 -- ./configure --help=short
 -- ./configure [probably options]
 -- make
 -- su -
 -- make install
 -- exit

Please look into the documentation to get a detailed explanation how to install
ONS with autotools. The documentation contains also information about how to
install ONS on supported platforms that do not use GNU autotools.

